I"¡<p>Implements the <a href="https://www.hunterdouglas.com/operating-systems/powerview-motorization/support">Hunter Douglas PowerView</a> platform scene control. It queries the PowerView Hub and Home Assistant displays them as scenes.</p>
<p>Scenes can be activated using the service <code>scene.turn_on</code>.</p>
<pre><code class="language-yaml"># Example configuration.yaml entry
scene:
  platform: hunterdouglas_powerview
  address: IP_ADDRESS
</code></pre>
<div class="config-vars">
  <h3><a class="title-link" name="configuration-variables" href="#configuration-variables"></a> Configuration Variables</h3>
  <dl class=''><dt><a class='title-link' name='address' href='#address'></a> address</dt><dd><p class='desc'><span class='type'>(<span class='string'>string</span>)</span><span class='required'>(Required)</span><span class='description'><p>IP address of the PowerView Hub, e.g., 192.168.1.10.</p>
</span></p></dd></dl>
</div>
<h2>Example Automations</h2>
<pre><code class="language-yaml">- alias: &quot;blinds closed at night&quot;
  trigger:
    platform: time
    at: &quot;18:00:00&quot;
  action:
    - service: scene.turn_on
      entity_id: scene.10877
</code></pre>
